This paper primarily focuses on the intersection of cybersecurity and machine learning, specifically in the context of anomaly detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses various machine learning algorithms and techniques, indicating a potential fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the importance of real-time data processing and visualization, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
